# Blender Shortcuts Skill

When the user asks any Blender shortcut / hotkey / "how to do X in Blender" question, use this reference.

## Rules of the road (read first)

- Blender is **hover-sensitive**: the shortcut applies to whichever editor the mouse is hovering over. Tell the user to hover their cursor over the 3D viewport before pressing keys.
- Since Blender 2.8, **left-click select** is the default (was right-click in 2.7x). Mention this if the user mentions old tutorials.
- Modal operators use **axis constraints**: press `X`, `Y`, or `Z` after `G`/`R`/`S` to constrain to an axis; press twice for the local axis. Hold `Shift+X` etc. to exclude an axis.
- Type a number while in a modal op to enter an exact value, then Enter.
- `Ctrl` while dragging = snap to grid/increments; `Shift` = fine control.

